#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.vonmises.rst:4
msgid "numpy.random.Generator.vonmises"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.vonmises.rst:8
msgid "method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:2
msgid "Draw samples from a von Mises distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:4
msgid ""
"Samples are drawn from a von Mises distribution with specified mode (mu) and "
"concentration (kappa), on the interval [-pi, pi]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:7
msgid ""
"The von Mises distribution (also known as the circular normal distribution) "
"is a continuous probability distribution on the unit circle.  It may be "
"thought of as the circular analogue of the normal distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:15
msgid "**mu**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:-1
msgid "float or array_like of floats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:15
msgid "Mode (\"center\") of the distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:18
msgid "**kappa**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:18
msgid "Concentration of the distribution, has to be >=0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:24
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:21
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is "
"returned if ``mu`` and ``kappa`` are both scalars. Otherwise, ``np."
"broadcast(mu, kappa).size`` samples are drawn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:35
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:-1
msgid "ndarray or scalar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:29
msgid "Drawn samples from the parameterized von Mises distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:40
msgid ":obj:`scipy.stats.vonmises`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:41
msgid ""
"probability density function, distribution, or cumulative density function, "
"etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:45
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:46
msgid "The probability density for the von Mises distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:48
msgid ""
"p(x) = \\frac{e^{\\kappa cos(x-\\mu)}}{2\\pi I_0(\\kappa)},\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:50
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mu` is the mode and :math:`\\kappa` the concentration, and :"
"math:`I_0(\\kappa)` is the modified Bessel function of order 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.vonmises:53
msgid ""
"The von Mises is named for Richard Edler von Mises, who was born in Austria-"
"Hungary, in what is now the Ukraine.  He fled to the United States in 1939 "
"and became a professor at Harvard.  He worked in probability theory, "
"aerodynamics, fluid mechanics, and philosophy of science."
msgstr ""

